      <akn:section eId="sec_28_4805_03">
        <akn:num>28-4805.03</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Transfers from income to principal for depreciation.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_03_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>For the purposes of this section, the term “depreciation” means a reduction in value due to wear, tear, decay, corrosion, or gradual obsolescence of a fixed asset having a useful life of more than one year.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_03_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A trustee may transfer to principal a reasonable amount of the net cash receipts from a principal asset that is subject to depreciation, but may not transfer any amount for depreciation:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_03_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>An amount transferred to principal need not be held as a separate fund.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
